  "_comment": "Third-tier signal (confidence 70-85): when title gives no cue, score the recipe's ingredient set against each region's characteristic-ingredient weights. The enricher sums weights per region, then sets confidence from the winning margin over the runner-up. Weights are small positive ints; an ingredient can mark several regions. Lowercased whole-word substring match against ingredient names. Expanded for under-represented cuisines so more of the non-Western recipes that DO exist in a Western-skewed dataset clear the confidence bar.",

